<title>INDIA: India's Infosys 1997/98 Q1 net up.</title>
<headline>India's Infosys 1997/98 Q1 net up.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to June 30, 1997</p>
<p>	     (in million rupees unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit		   92.20 vs     45.50</p>
<p>    Total income		458.10 vs    264.30</p>
<p>    Overseas income	   437.90 vs    234.80</p>
<p>    Domestic income	    15.50 vs     16.50</p>
<p>    Other income		  4.70 vs     13.00</p>
<p>    Total expenses	    320.80 vs    187.30</p>
<p>    Interest			 nil vs	1.40</p>
<p>    Depreciation		 35.50 vs     19.60</p>
<p>    Taxation			9.60 vs     10.50</p>
<p>Note: Infosys Technologies Ltd is one of India's leading software companies. The results are audited, the company said in a statement.</p>
<p>The company said its revenue rose 73 percent in the first quarter of 1997/98 (April-June) and net profit rose 103 percent over the same period last year.</p>
<p>-- Bombay newsroom +91-22-265 9000</p>
